                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d308">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">White</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Hay</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Embassy</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">London</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1904-04-27">
                            <hi rend="italic">April 27, 1904</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>(Mr. White reports that Lord Lansdowne has addressed a note to the Russian
                    ambassador in London embodying a reservation similar to the reply of the United
                    States to the Russian declaration respecting wireless telegraphy which Mr. White
                    communicated to him yesterday.)</p>
            </div>
